<p>
DeviantART&#39;s Marketing department is seeking a self-starting Marketing Assistant who wishes to join a team of geeky individuals and assist in all levels of workplace organization.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate would be all four Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles rolled into one.</p>
<p>
<strong>Leonardo - A leader in project management:</strong></p>
<p>
* Keeps track of follow-up action points from meetings and conference calls<br />
* Performs follow-up with other employees related to their projects and tasks<br />
* Researches and documents new products, business ideas, services, and events</p>
<p>
<strong>Michaelangelo - A dude in tune with listening to the community:</strong></p>
<p>
* Monitors online community issues, trends, and activity<br />
* Assists with writing and proofreading internal and external communications<br />
* Assists with the development and execution of new promotional campaigns<br />
* Data collection and analysis</p>
<p>
<strong>Raphael - A cool head in the workplace, carrying out administrative duties with personal flair:</strong></p>
<p>
* Organization of work calendars, appointments, meetings, and scheduled calls<br />
* Assists in prioritization of emails, calls, IMs, and other communications<br />
* Researches and books travel arrangements<br />
* Document organization, filing, and scanning<br />
* Maintains department contact list and ensures details kept up-to-date<br />
* Performs other related tasks and special projects as required</p>
<p>
<strong>Donatello - A team player who knows their way around a computer:</strong></p>
<p>
* Must be *HIGHLY* computer and Internet savvy<br />
* Familiarity with HTML, CSS, and Photoshop a plus<br />
* Strong working knowledge of basic programs, including Word, Excel, and PowerPoint<br />
* Excellent English communication skills<br />
* Incredibly competent and imaginative writer<br />
* Self-motivated, driven, and able to articulate his/her vision<br />
* Must be able to multitask, have a positive attitude, and sense of humor<br />
* Capable of working independently as well as part of a team<br />
* Must exercise good judgment in handling confidential/sensitive information</p>
<p>
<strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<p>
Ideal candidate does not necessarily need to love the Ninja Turtles, but the type of person who does would fit in quite well here. Plus, we offer these benefits:</p>
<p>
* Salary commensurate with experience<br />
* Healthcare and 401(k) benefits<br />
* Potential for stock options</p>
