			<description><![CDATA[<p>
DeviantART&#39;s Marketing department is looking for a Manager, Marketing/Web Analytics, to help organize, augment, and maintain our Web analytics and business intelligence efforts.&nbsp; We are looking for someone who is data driven, skilled in Web traffic and user data analytics, technically savvy, a strong communicator, highly organized, and self-motivated.&nbsp; This highly visible role is a great opportunity for the right candidate to help deviantART improve decision-making and assist in the identification of new opportunities.</p>
<p>
<strong>What we&#39;re looking for:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A strong understanding of online analytics and how to synthesize large amounts of behavioral data</li>
<li>
Exposure to user-centric product development and design</li>
<li>
Experience working with multiple data sources (online, offline, site analytics, media, e-mail) to analyze marketing campaign performance</li>
<li>
Know-how around developing and managing KPIs / Marketing Scorecards for product launches and the ability to make recommendations for improvements</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Example responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Support the analytical and reporting needs of the Marketing team -- collaborating to create, evaluate, and improve data-driven marketing strategies</li>
<li>
Move deviantART&#39;s Web/traffic analytics needs forward by managing Google Analytics, and ensuring the information is implemented and managed correctly</li>
<li>
Add URL campaign tags and event tracking to user interface components to gauge feature utilization, success, and conversion</li>
<li>
Establish baselines and A/B test funnels for site launches, user interaction with products, etc., and track unverified user behavior</li>
<li>
Communicate and address data anomalies, gaps, issues, etc., and present solutions to improve user experience</li>
<li>
Recognize how users interact with our products by reviewing past results and post analysis in order to help the team make better decisions</li>
<li>
Support all facets of the decision-making process and work with our technology teams to identify gaps in data capture strategy and implement enhancements</li>
<li>
Take responsibility for the development, standardization, and production of reports that track effectiveness of Marketing initiatives</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
4 to 6 + years of work experience, with proven quantitative and analytical skills</li>
<li>
Background in multivariate product testing, SEO, SEM, e-mail, and social media marketing</li>
<li>
Highly skilled at using Google Analytics and Microsoft Excel -- knowledge of SQL is a plus</li>
<li>
Strong track record of analytical problem-solving, and setting and achieving goals with a drive towards actionable insights</li>
<li>
Intimate knowledge of the nuances of digital tracking technologies coupled with adept data management skills</li>
<li>
Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Must be able to interact cross-functionally with both technical and non-technical people</li>
<li>
Ability to remain focused-yet-flexible in a fast-paced Internet company environment</li>
<li>
Strong project management skills with the ability to independently manage multiple efforts</li>
<li>
Must be able to work from our Hollywood, CA headquarters</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Salary commensurate with experience</li>
<li>
Healthcare and 401(k) benefits</li>
<li>
Potential for stock options</li>
</ul>
