			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	DeviantART was created to entertain, inspire, and empower the artist in all of us and today is the leading destination on the Internet for creativity and the arts.&nbsp; The Creative Director position at deviantART is very challenging, but is also an amazing job for the right person.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	The job of Creative Director is bigger and more important than any one task. We&rsquo;re looking for someone who can help shape and refine the creative brain of the Company and build a stronger creative conscience. Someone capable of finding ways to model the creative process throughout the organization so that people know what it looks like when they see it.&nbsp; Someone who can help take great ideas and breathe life into them &ndash; making them real. Someone who sees things differently from other people &ndash; visualizing design and development much like an art form and knows what it takes to deliver world-class creative solutions.</p>
<p>
	So if you understand how to connect on an emotional level with a creative, passionate and artistic community whose members range from professional artists to aspirational artists; if you can bring cutting-edge thinking, high creative aesthetic, and advanced knowledge of Web design, usability, social media, and other digital applications to deliver a best in-class experience for the customer and can demonstrate originality, innovation, problem-solving, and personal expression&hellip;..deviantART might just be the place for you.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Everyday tasks include:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Leading the creative development process and workflow, providing creative feedback, and ensuring business objectives are supported through high quality design.</li>
	<li>
		Working with business partners to assess project needs, developing strategies for digital/interactive programs. Following through with effective design, problem solving, and creative solutions.</li>
	<li>
		Being able to work collaboratively in a fast paced environment, while managing multiple people and projects, and develop strong working relationships with internal and external partners.</li>
	<li>
		Maintaining a productive, supportive environment for the Creative team, and providing both creative and technical expertise and leadership.</li>
	<li>
		Staying current with the quickly evolving digital universe and possessing enthusiasm for interfacing with internal business partners, creative peers and external agencies/vendors.</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrating a passion for strategic problem solving and utilizing a deep understanding of Web/digital design and usability to develop fully integrated campaigns.</li>
	<li>
		Helping us infuse the brand identity into corporate culture and office design &ndash; help us &quot;live the brand.&quot;</li>
	<li>
		Establishing and documenting guidelines, while striving for process simplification.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Bachelor Degree in Creative Design/Graphics preferred</li>
	<li>
		8 to 10 years of Creative Design experience with a digital focus required</li>
	<li>
		5+ years progressive experience with a global brand or client where digital creative is integral part of brand communication</li>
	<li>
		Broad design skill set that includes: web design, email, social, mobile and other digital media types</li>
	<li>
		Direct and manage a high-volume digital design process, while adhering to schedules in a fast-paced environment</li>
	<li>
		Fluent understanding of current Web, email and interactive trends, technologies and best practices</li>
	<li>
		Ability to apply digital design best practices to ensure effective projects crafted to engage customers, build relationship and loyalty, inspire confidence, and drive sales</li>
	<li>
		Ability to develop strong working relationships with internal and external partners. Team leadership skills and ability to work cross-functional teams</li>
	<li>
		Capacity to make decisions on a daily basis that ensure both efficiency and creative quality. Set expectations and standards (build a culture) for creative team attitude, behavior and teamwork</li>
	<li>
		Strong team player with enthusiasm, positive attitude and the willingness to do what it takes to get the job done, which may include extended hours when necessary to meet deadlines</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	This position is located in our Los Angeles office.&nbsp; It is a dual report to the CEO and the VP of Marketing.&nbsp; The current staff includes 4 designers and 1 project manager.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	If you have the experience and the skill, please contact us with portfolio links, resume, and cover letter.</p>
