<strong>Description:</strong></p>
<p>
Are you interested in working for one of the largest and most vibrant community properties on the Web?&nbsp; Do you have what it takes to help support Product Marketing for the Web&#39;s leading creative destination?&nbsp; Do you consider yourself a technical prowess who surfs the Web night and day?&nbsp; Do you have a natural passion and interest in supporting creativity and the arts?&nbsp; If you answered yes to all of the above, we want to talk to you!</p>
<p>
DeviantART was created to entertain, inspire, and empower the artist in all of us.&nbsp; Founded in August 2000, deviantART is the largest online social network for artists and art enthusiasts with over 20 million registered members, attracting 45 million unique visitors per month.&nbsp; These metrics position deviantART in the top 125 of all websites by traffic.</p>
<p>
As a community destination, deviantART is a platform that allows emerging and established artists to exhibit, promote, and share their works within a peer community dedicated to the arts.&nbsp; The site&#39;s vibrant social network environment receives over 100,000 daily uploads of original artwork, ranging from traditional media, such as painting and sculpture, to digital art, pixel art, films and anime.</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Summary:</strong></p>
<p>
As a Product Marketing Assistant for deviantART, you will be responsible for planning and executing campaigns to help the growth and development of the deviantART community and its features.</p>
<p>
A Product Marketing Assistant provides an invaluable service to the organization and truly helps define the vision for new site initiatives, and plays a pivotal role in managing the flow of bringing them to market.&nbsp; This position works closely with the heads of deviantART&#39;s Marketing and Product divisions and is a position for someone who is already familiar with how deviantART works -- understands the community, and genuinely wants to help develop and promote features and services that aid artists and art enthusiasts.</p>
<p>
A Product Marketing Assistant is responsible for servicing the department as it expands to meet its goal of informing and educating the community about deviantART&#39;s ever-evolving products and features.&nbsp; You will handle research and organization, and will work closely with several internal departments, as well as the community, to strengthen efforts relating to the consistent updates of deviantART sitewide features.</p>
<p>
<strong>Example Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Brainstorms, researches, and documents new product opportunities, business ideas, and services</li>
<li>
Monitors online community issues, trends, and activity</li>
<li>
Assists with writing and proofreading internal and external communications</li>
<li>
Assists with the development and execution of new marketing campaigns</li>
<li>
Plans and executes product launches</li>
<li>
Data collection and analysis</li>
<li>
Keeps track of follow-up action points from meetings and conference calls</li>
<li>
Performs follow-up with other employees related to their projects and tasks</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Must be *HIGHLY* computer and Internet savvy</li>
